Bank of America Corporation Puts Non-US Wealth Arm Up For Sale-Reuters
Tuesday, 17 Apr 2012 12:58pm EDT
Reuters reported that Bank of America Corporation's Bank of America Merrill Lynch has put its wealth management units outside the United States up for sale, hoping to bring in up to $3 billion for the sub-scale business. Bank of America was looking to sell the unit as a whole and the deal could bring in up to $3 billion, or more than 3% of assets under management.Â 
